page.title: 09LIVING IN WINTERTON
page.content: It was 6.30 am and my Dad woke me up with a shout that could wake up the whole house. I got out of bed and got my school clothes on. Next I sneaked down the stairs trying not to wake my little brothers up who are lazy bones. When I got down my Dad had gone to work and so I had to make my own breakfast. After I had finished it was spot on 7am. Soon my big brother got up so I decided to get ready for school. I set off for school at 8.30. School is good because I like doing maths and English. Also I like dinner because of the puddings. At dinner play I play football. When school is over I walk home with my friend and his brother. When I get home I have my tea then play football outside with my friend. After 3-4 hours I go in and watch TV. After I have watched what I want I go to bed.
